verbose_text: Our data showed that the substitution of TRIM9-WT allowed Trim9 -/- primary neurons to regain their ability to suppress stimulation induced NF-kappaB signaling, whereas the substitution of the TRIM9-SA mutant showed little or no effect on NF-kappaB signaling (XREF_FIG, XREF_FIG, and XREF_SUPPLEMENTARY - XREF_SUPPLEMENTARY).
